en a number of selfhelp books on the hour theme some of which have appeared on the new york times wall street journal and usa today bestseller lists starting with the hour workweek ferriss is also an angel investor or an advisor to facebook twitter stumbleupon evernote and uber among other companies tim is also host of the popular podcast the tim ferriss show contents  early life  career  brainquicken  television  publishing  investor and advisor  author  the hour workweek  the hour body  the hour chef  tools of titans  the tim ferriss show  influence  the tim ferriss effect  philanthropy  psychedelic research  personal life  references  external links early lifeedit ferriss grew up in east hampton new york and graduated from st pauls school in concord new hampshire he received a degree in east asian studies from princeton university in  after graduation ferriss worked in sales at a data storage company ferriss began building his own internet business brainquicken while still employed at the company careeredit brainquickenedit in  ferriss founded brainquicken an online nutritional supplements company which made a product that was marketed as both bodyquick and brain quicken it was claimed that this product would dramatically increase short term memory and reaction speed taking effect within  minutes in  he sold the company to a londonbased private equity firm it was the experiences ferriss had running brainquicken that led him to write the hour workweek televisionedit in december  ferriss had a pilot on the history channel called trial by fire where he had one week to attempt to learn a skill normally learned over the course of many years in the pilot episode he practiced yabusame the japanese art of horseback archery in december  his television series the tim ferriss experiment debuted on hln although there were  episodes shot only a portion of those were shown on television the show was released in its entirety on itunes publishingedit in november  ferriss began an audiobook publishing venture tim ferriss publishing the first book published was vagabonding by rolf potts other books include the obstacle is the way by ryan holiday daily rituals by mason currey and what i learned losing a million dollars by jim paul and brendan moynihan investor and advisoredit ferriss is an angel investor and advisor to startups he has invested or advised in startups such as stumbleupon posterous evernote dailyburn shopify reputationcom trippy and taskrabbit he is a preseed money advisor to uber a company cofounded by garrett camp the founder of stumbleupon which ferriss also advises in september  ferriss raised  in under an hour to invest in shyp by forming a syndicate on angellist ferriss ended up raising over  through his backers and shyp raised a total of  million the new york times listed ferriss among their notable angel investors while cnn said he was one of the planets leading angel investors in technology authoredit ferriss is the author of four books the hour workweek the hour body the hour chef and tools of titans the first two were no  new york times bestsellers and the third was a no  wall street journal bestseller the hour workweekedit main article the hour workweek ferriss developed the ideas present in the hour workweek while working hour days at brainquicken the hour workweek was rejected by  publishers in  random house the th publisher released the book through its crown imprint before release ferriss was an unknown he marketed the book heavily through bloggers with whom he created personal relationships the hour workweek would reach no  on the new york times bestseller list no  on the wall street journal bestseller list and no  on the businessweek bestseller list it has currently sold over  copies and has spent nearly  years on the new york times bestseller list the book received both positive and negative reviews leslie garner of the telegraph noted that with a punchy writing style and a higher literacy level than most flas