erriss  wikipedia tim ferriss from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search not to be confused with the science writer timothy ferris or the musician tim farriss this article contains content that is written like an advertisement please help improve it by removing promotional content and inappropriate external links and by adding encyclopedic content written from a neutral point of view february  learn how and when to remove this template message tim ferriss born timothy ferriss  july   age  east hampton new york us occupation writer author entrepreneur public speaker alma mater princeton university genre selfhelp personal development selfexperimentation notable works the hour workweek the hour body the hour chef timothy tim ferriss born july   is an american author entrepreneur selfproclaimed human guinea pig and public speaker he has written a number of selfhelp books on the hour theme some of which have appeared on the new york times wall street journal and usa today bestseller lists starting with the hour workweek ferriss is also an angel investor or an advisor to facebook twitter stumbleupon evernote and uber among other companies tim is also host of the popular podcast the tim ferriss show contents  early life  career  brainquicken  television  publishing  investor and advisor  author  the hour workweek  the hour body  the hour chef  tools of titans  the tim ferriss show  influence  the tim ferriss effect  philanthropy  psychedelic research  personal life  references  external links early lifeedit ferriss grew up in east hampton new york and graduated from st pauls school in concord new hampshire he received a degree in east asian studies from princeton university in  after graduation ferriss worked in sales at a data storage company ferriss began building his own internet business brainquicken while still employed at the company careeredit brainquickenedit in  ferriss founded brainquicken an online nutritional supplements company which made a product that was marketed as both bodyquick and brain quicken it was claimed that this product would dramatically increase short term memory and reaction speed taking effect within  minutes in  he sold the company to a londonbased private equity firm it was the experiences ferriss had running brainquicken that led him to write the hour workweek televisionedit in december  ferriss had a pilot on the history channel called trial by fire where he had one week to attempt to learn a skill normally learned over the course of many years in the pilot episode he practiced yabusame the japanese art of horseback archery in december  his television series the tim ferriss experiment debuted on hln although there were  episodes shot only a portion of those were shown on television the show was released in its entirety on itunes publishingedit in november  ferriss began an audiobook publishing venture tim ferriss publishing the first book published was vagabonding by rolf potts other books include the obstacle is the way by ryan holiday daily rituals by mason currey and what i learned losing a million dollars by jim paul and brendan moynihan investor and advisoredit ferriss is an angel investor and advisor to startups he has invested or advised in startups such as stumbleupon posterous evernote dailyburn shopify reputationcom trippy and taskrabbit he is a preseed money advisor to uber a company cofounded by garrett camp the founder of stumbleupon which ferriss also advises in september  ferriss raised  in under an hour to invest in shyp by forming a syndicate on angellist ferriss ended up raising over  through his backers and shyp raised a total of  million the new york times listed ferriss among their notable angel investors while cnn said he was one of the planets leading angel investors in technology authoredit ferriss is the author of four books the hour workweek the hour body the hour chef and tools of titans the first two were no  new york times bestsellers and the third was a no  wall street journal bestseller the hour workweekedit main article the hour workweek ferriss developed the ideas present in the hour workweek while working hour days at brainquicken the hour workweek was rejected by  publishers in  random house the th publisher released the book through its crown imprint before release ferriss was an unknown he marketed the book heavily through bloggers with whom he created personal relationships the hour workweek would reach no  on the new york times bestseller list no  on the wall street journal bestseller list and no  on the businessweek bestseller list it has currently sold over  copies and has spent nearly  years on the new york times bestseller list the book received both positive and negative reviews leslie garner of the telegraph noted that with a punchy writing style and a higher literacy level than most flashinthepan gurus ferriss has struck a chord with his critique of workerss slavish devotion to corporations ferriss book skillfully compartmentalises then pathologises workerss unhealthy relationships with office life dylan tweney of wired wrote nearly every idea taken to extreme no sense of work being anything more than a paycheck in  the hour workweek expanded and updated was released by random house and included multiple case studies authored by people who have utilized ferrisss methods the hour bodyedit main article the hour body in december  ferrisss second book the hour body an uncommon guide to rapid fatloss incredible sex and becoming superhuman was published by crown the book covers more than  topics including rapid fat loss increasing strength boosting endurance and polyphasic sleep ferriss also introduces his version of the slowcarb diet which involves the elimination of starches and anything sweet including fruit and all artificial sweeteners and a strong preference for lean protein legumes and vegetables for the book ferriss interviewed more than  experts over a threeyear period the experts ranged from doctors to athletes to blackmarket drug salesmen he said that he had recorded every workout he had done since the age of  and from  three years before his first book was published he had tracked a variety of blood chemistry measurements including insulin levels hemoglobin ac and free testosterone in the book ferriss wrote about using anabolic steroids specifically a number of lowdose therapies including testosterone cypionate under medical supervision following shoulder surgery as well as using stacks consisting of testosterone enanthate sustanon  hgh decadurabolin cytomel and other unnamed ingredients while training the hour body debuted at no  on the new york times best seller list it peaked at no  on both the wall street journal and usa todays lists and was one of amazoncoms top  bestselling books for december  and january  as part of the press for the book ferriss appeared as a guest on the dr oz show and abcs the view the hour chefedit main article the hour chef ferrisss third book the hour chef the simple path to cooking like a pro learning anything and living the good life was released by amazon publishing in november the hour chef contains practical cooking and recipe tips and uses the skill of cooking to explain his methods for accelerated learning which he calls metalearning the book reached no  on the wall street journal bestseller list in its first week of issue however many brick and mortar bookstores including independents and barnes  noble chose to not stock the book due to their objections to the business practices of amazon publishing this required ferriss to make arrangements with nonconventional partners including bittorrent panera bread and taskrabbit in order to distribute the book in particular ferriss teamed up with bittorrent to distribute an exclusive bundle of hour chef content including excerpts from the book photos interviews and unpublished content which was downloaded over  times the first week after release the audiobook featured guest narration by neil gaiman tools of titansedit ferriss fourth book tools of titans was released on december   by houghton mifflin harcourt the books content consists of tactics and routines from some of the most popular guests on the tim ferriss show podcast tools of titans debuted at  on the new york times bestseller list the book was the first podcastbased book to debut on the new york times list the tim ferriss showedit ferriss has been called the oprah of audio due to the influence and reach of his podcast the tim ferriss show which as of  had over  million downloads it covers topics ranging from personal and character development to exercise routines acting venture capital and metaphysics the show was voted “best podcast episode of ” by users of product hunt in their golden kitty awards influenceedit the new yorker described ferriss as this generations selfhelp guru comparing ferriss and his books to authors of similar influence of previous generations—napoleon hill norman vincent peale stephen covey and spencer johnson wired called ferriss “the superman of silicon valley” the new york times said ferriss was somewhere between retired general electric chairman and ceo jack welch and a buddhist monk in  newsweek declared ferriss the worlds best guinea pig he has been named among newsweeks digital power index  as the seventh most powerful online personality fortunes  under  one of fast companys most innovative business people of  and a henry crown fellow by the aspen institute both the hour body and the hour workweek are in the  most highlighted books of all time on amazon kindle in  he was named wireds greatest selfpromoter of all time the tim ferriss effectedit in  author michael ellsberg coined the phrase the tim ferriss effect in a forbes profile the phrase was used to describe the influence a blog post on ferriss site had on the sales of ellsbergs book ellsberg found that his post on ferriss blog sold more books than a piece in the new york times and a threeminute segment on cnn ryan holiday who had previously been hired by ferriss to assist with the promotion of the hour body and the hour chef said this effect helped to sell  copies of his own book in the weeks following its release the clothing brand mizzenmain wrote about the effect on their clothing sales stating that a mention on the podcast boosted exposure and sales for the brand more than a profile in the new york times an announcement in the wall street journal or a full page ad in esquire philanthropyedit ferriss is a charity advocate and a member of the national advisory council of the public school nonprofit donorschoose his projects and donations have raised more than  for underfunded public school teachers and classroom projects and his campaigns such as dedicating his birthday to raising funds and heading litliberation to increase literacy worldwide have impacted more than  students in march  ferriss flash funded  school projects posted on donorschooseorg in coordination with stephen colbert in october  build boston a notforprofit organization that uses entrepreneurship to equip boston youth for high school and college success honored ferriss with the annual builder award for innovation and entrepreneurship for his work in education reform ferriss is also on the advisory board of the nonprofit questbridge along with linkedin founder reid hoffman david sze and others questbridge was created in  to connect disadvantaged students with elite colleges and helps place over  students per year psychedelic researchedit ferriss has raised funds for psychedelic studies at institutions such as johns hopkins university school of medicine in  ferriss donated at least  to research psychedelic drugs for the treatment of major depression personal lifeedit ferriss lives in san francisco california he holds a guinness world record in argentine tango ferriss has stated that prior to his writing career he won in the  lb weight class at the  usawkf national sanshou chinese kickboxing championship through a process of shoving opponents out of the ring and by dramatically dehydrating himself before weigh in and then rehydrating before the fight in order to compete several classes below his actual weight – a practice known as weight cutting referencesedit  grant elaine appelton march    questions for productivity guru tim ferriss us news and world report retrieved april     hartley matt april   ottawas shopify launches  buildabusiness promotion national post   a b c chalupa andrea maney kevin october   tim ferriss wants you to get a life abc news   a b c hardcover business best sellers the new york times august     a b best selling books wall street journal august     debbie kelley february   the hour workweek colorado springs gazette      hour work week usa today march     bestselling books week ended july  wall street journal   a b c taylor ihsan january   best sellers hardcover advice  misc the new york times   streitfeld david august   amazon set to publish tim ferriss the new york times   a b bestselling books week ended nov  wall street journal november       wauters robin april   tim the hour workweek ferriss on angel investing video techcrunch   bertoni steven april   tim ferriss on facebook twitter and building a huge web brand forbes   timothy ferriss ’ princeton alumni weekly hall cornelia may   ferriss  takes the day off the daily princetonian   a b c rosenbloom stephanie march   the world according to tim ferriss the new york times   httpbrainresearchsupplementscombrainquickenbybodyquickllc  httpsamazonawscomquarkbasetestcombrainquickencomsnapshotjpg bowers brent june   in the hunt the hectic chronicles new york times  ferriss tim september   how i work cnn money retrieved april    tim ferriss wants you to get a life abc news october    warrillow john october   why tim ferriss sold his muse the globe and mail toronto  warrillow john november   why tim ferriss sold his muse inc magazine   marketing ideas  tim ferriss trial by fi